category: Gnome
requires: python python-cairo python-gi python-pyatspi girepository-Wnck3.0
sdesc: "GNOME interactive accessibility explorer"
ldesc: "Accerciser is an interactive Python accessibility explorer for 
the GNOME desktop. It uses AT-SPI to inspect and control widgets, 
allowing you to check if an application is providing correct information 
to assistive technologies and automated test frameworks. Accerciser has 
a simple plugin framework which you can use to create custom views of 
accessibility information."
